    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1965-05-27T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1965-05-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="253"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d253">
                <head>253. Memorandum From <persName corresp="#p_KRW2" type="from">Robert W.
                        Komer</persName> of the National Security Council Staff to the President’s
                    Special Assistant for National Security Affairs (<persName corresp="#p_BMG2"
                        type="to">Bundy</persName>)<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d253fn1"
                        >Source: Johnson Library, National Security File, Country File, Ghana, Vol.
                        II, Cables, 3/64–2/66. Secret.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1965-05-27">May 27, 1965</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p rend="flushleft">McGB—</p>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_FYI1">FYI</gloss>, we may have a pro-Western coup in Ghana
                    soon. Certain key military and police figures have been planning one for some
                    time, and Ghana’s deteriorating economic condition may provide the spark.</p>
                <p>The plotters are keeping us briefed, and State thinks we’re more on the inside
                    than the British. While we’re not directly involved (I’m told), we and other
                    Western countries (including France) have been helping to set up the situation
                    by ignoring <persName corresp="#p_NK2">Nkrumah</persName>’s pleas for economic
                    aid. The new <gloss target="#t_OCAM1">OCAM</gloss> (Francophone) group’s refusal
                    to attend any <gloss target="#t_OAU1">OAU</gloss> meeting in Accra (because of
                        <persName corresp="#p_NK2">Nkrumah</persName>’s plotting) will further
                    isolate him. All in all, looks good.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName>
                            <hi rend="strong">RWK</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
